      "message": "You could either do it like this (after):\n\n    .mw-ui-button {\n        // some css\n    }\n    .mw-ui-button:hover {\n        // some css for hover\n    }\n\nOr, like in this patch (inside):\n\n    .mw-ui-button {\n        // some css\n        \n        \u0026:hover {\n            // some css for hover\n        }\n    }\n\nSpot the \u0026!\n\nAnything nested inside usually refers to a child element. Quite like normal css\u0027s:\n\n    .parent-class .child class\n\nAnything nested inside, with an \u0026, applies to that same element. Quite like normal css\u0027s:\n\n    .parent-class.another-parent-class\n\nor, in this case:\n\n    .parent-class:hover\n\nSo having \u0026:hover inside .mw-ui-button, will translate to:\n\n    .mw-ui-button:hover",
